  "body": "Duplicating https://github.com/nodejs/http-parser/issues/517 to envoy.\r\nPrior to making changes to http-parser library wanted to confirm that proposed change looks reasonable to envoy maintainers.\r\n\r\n\r\nCurrent implementation of nodejs/http-parser rejects requests with Transfer-Encoding: chunked and Content-Length headers with HPE_UNEXPECTED_CONTENT_LENGTH.\r\nhttps://github.com/nodejs/http-parser/blob/master/http_parser.c#L1804-L1815\r\n\r\nBut per https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230#section-3.3.3 that's a valid http request, Content-Length must be ignored:\r\n\r\n       If a message is received with both a Transfer-Encoding and a\r\n       Content-Length header field, the Transfer-Encoding overrides the\r\n       Content-Length. \r\n\r\n",
